<paragraph blockId="18.[377,927,137,194]" box="[563,678,170,194]" pageId="18" pageNumber="3967">
(
<figureCitation box="[571,670,170,194]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="18.[138,198,1611,1630]" captionTargetBox="[139,1185,890,1573]" captionTargetId="figure-102@18.[138,1186,888,1575]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 6. Phortica glabtabula Chen and Gao, sp. nov., „. (A) Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (B) 10th sternite and additional plate (frontal view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal median rod (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221188" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221188/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="3967">Figure 6</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[138,243,250,274]" box="[138,243,250,274]" pageId="18" pageNumber="3967">
<emphasis box="[138,243,250,274]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="3967">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[138,1185,299,453]" pageId="18" pageNumber="3967">
Secondary process of paramere small, with one sensillum subapically (
<figureCitation box="[960,1081,299,323]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="18.[138,198,1611,1630]" captionTargetBox="[139,1185,890,1573]" captionTargetId="figure-102@18.[138,1186,888,1575]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 6. Phortica glabtabula Chen and Gao, sp. nov., „. (A) Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (B) 10th sternite and additional plate (frontal view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal median rod (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221188" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221188/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="3967">Figure 6C</figureCitation>
); branch of aedeagal basal bridge sclerotized along outer margin, with about seven acute, marginal projections (
<figureCitation box="[282,404,364,388]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="18.[138,198,1611,1630]" captionTargetBox="[139,1185,890,1573]" captionTargetId="figure-102@18.[138,1186,888,1575]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 6. Phortica glabtabula Chen and Gao, sp. nov., „. (A) Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (B) 10th sternite and additional plate (frontal view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal median rod (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221188" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221188/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="3967">Figure 6C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[138,1185,299,453]" pageId="18" pageNumber="3967">
Some characters commonly seen in 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen &amp; Gao &amp; Wen, 2005" authorityName="Chen &amp; Gao &amp; Wen" authorityYear="2005" box="[612,745,397,421]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="3967" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uncinata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[612,745,397,421]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="3967">P. uncinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[759,857,397,421]" pageId="18" pageNumber="3967" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are not referred to in the following description.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[138,259,510,534]" box="[138,259,510,534]" pageId="18" pageNumber="3967">
<emphasis box="[138,259,510,534]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="3967">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[138,903,559,583]" box="[138,903,559,583]" pageId="18" pageNumber="3967">
<emphasis box="[138,206,559,583]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="3967">Head.</emphasis>
Frons brown, pale lower. Face, gena and postgena brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[138,591,624,648]" box="[138,591,624,648]" pageId="18" pageNumber="3967">
<emphasis box="[138,226,624,648]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="3967">Thorax.</emphasis>
Anepisternum lacking setulae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[138,638,689,713]" box="[138,638,689,713]" pageId="18" pageNumber="3967">
<emphasis box="[138,195,689,712]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="3967">Legs.</emphasis>
Yellow except femora mostly brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[138,1185,753,842]" pageId="18" pageNumber="3967">
<emphasis box="[138,249,753,777]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="3967">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Second tergite laterally with brown-black patches; third and fifth with medially protruded and sublaterally interrupted, broad, brown-black bands along posterior margins; sixth nearly entirely black.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221188" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5221188" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221188/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="3967" startId="18.[138,198,1611,1630]" targetBox="[139,1185,890,1573]" targetPageId="18">
<paragraph blockId="18.[138,1185,1611,1683]" pageId="18" pageNumber="3967">
Figure 6. 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen and Gao" authorityName="Chen and Gao" authorityYear="2005" box="[233,549,1611,1630]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="3967" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glabtabula" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[233,402,1611,1630]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="3967">Phortica glabtabula</emphasis>
Chen and Gao
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[559,635,1611,1630]" pageId="18" pageNumber="3967" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<emphasis box="[645,659,1612,1631]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="3967">„</emphasis>
. (A) Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (B) 10th sternite and additional plate (frontal view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal median rod (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="19.[125,1172,136,288]" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">
<emphasis box="[125,318,136,160]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">Male terminalia.</emphasis>
Epandrium with pubescence anteroventrally, and 11–12 setae near posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[338,459,168,192]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="18.[138,198,1611,1630]" captionTargetBox="[139,1185,890,1573]" captionTargetId="figure-102@18.[138,1186,888,1575]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 6. Phortica glabtabula Chen and Gao, sp. nov., „. (A) Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (B) 10th sternite and additional plate (frontal view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal median rod (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221188" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221188/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">Figure 6A</figureCitation>
). Surstylus with pubescence, and dense setae, and about 20 apically round prensisetae (
<figureCitation box="[448,569,200,224]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="18.[138,198,1611,1630]" captionTargetBox="[139,1185,890,1573]" captionTargetId="figure-102@18.[138,1186,888,1575]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 6. Phortica glabtabula Chen and Gao, sp. nov., „. (A) Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (B) 10th sternite and additional plate (frontal view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal median rod (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221188" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221188/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">Figure 6A</figureCitation>
). Vertical process of gonopod very large, narrowed and sclerotized apically (
<figureCitation box="[413,535,232,256]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="18.[138,198,1611,1630]" captionTargetBox="[139,1185,890,1573]" captionTargetId="figure-102@18.[138,1186,888,1575]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 6. Phortica glabtabula Chen and Gao, sp. nov., „. (A) Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (B) 10th sternite and additional plate (frontal view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal median rod (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221188" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221188/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">Figure 6C</figureCitation>
). Paramere distally pubescent, with one sensillum and two teeth apically (
<figureCitation box="[348,470,264,288]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="18.[138,198,1611,1630]" captionTargetBox="[139,1185,890,1573]" captionTargetId="figure-102@18.[138,1186,888,1575]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 6. Phortica glabtabula Chen and Gao, sp. nov., „. (A) Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (B) 10th sternite and additional plate (frontal view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal median rod (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221188" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221188/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">Figure 6C</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal median rod slender (
<figureCitation box="[850,972,264,288]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="18.[138,198,1611,1630]" captionTargetBox="[139,1185,890,1573]" captionTargetId="figure-102@18.[138,1186,888,1575]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 6. Phortica glabtabula Chen and Gao, sp. nov., „. (A) Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (B) 10th sternite and additional plate (frontal view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal median rod (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221188" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221188/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="3968">Figure 6C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
